Note:
Runa Standard Library: Go Type Information Parsing Support

Production-grade helper functions for parsing Go reflection data and type information.
These functions provide complete Go method and field extraction with proper error handling,
memory safety, and performance optimizations for interop operations.
:End Note

Import "../../string" as String
Import "../../collections" as Collections

Note: Go Method Information Parsing
Process parse_go_method_info that takes type_data as String and offset as Integer returns Optional[GoMethod]:
    If offset + 32 is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty
    Note: Parse method structure: name_len(4) + name_data + signature_len(4) + signature + flags(4) + receiver_type(4) + method_index(4)
    Let name_len be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, offset)
    If name_len is equal to 0 or name_len is greater than 256:
    Return Empty Let name_offset be offset + 4
    If name_offset + name_len is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty Let method_name be String::substring(type_data, name_offset, name_len) Let sig_len_offset be name_offset + name_len
    Let signature_len be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, sig_len_offset)
    If signature_len is greater than 512: Note: Reasonable signature limit
    Return Empty Let signature_offset be sig_len_offset + 4
    If signature_offset + signature_len is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty Let signature be String::substring(type_data, signature_offset, signature_len) Let flags_offset be signature_offset + signature_len
    Let method_flags be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, flags_offset) Let receiver_type_offset be flags_offset + 4
    Let receiver_type_id be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, receiver_type_offset) Let method_index_offset be receiver_type_offset + 4
    Let method_index be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, method_index_offset)
    Note: Parse method visibility and properties from flags
    Let is_exported be (method_flags and 1) is not equal to 0
    Let is_variadic be (method_flags and 2) is not equal to 0
    Let is_embedded be (method_flags and 4) is not equal to 0
    Note: Parse signature to extract parameters and return types
    Let parsed_signature be parse_go_method_signature(signature) Let go_method be GoMethod with:
    name as method_name,
    signature as signature,
    is_exported as is_exported,
    is_variadic as is_variadic,
    is_embedded as is_embedded,
    parameter_types as parsed_signature.parameters,
    return_types as parsed_signature.returns,
    receiver_type as receiver_type_id,
    method_index as method_index,
    method_flags as method_flags Return Some with value go_method

Process parse_go_field_info that takes type_data as String and offset as Integer returns Optional[GoField]:
    If offset + 24 is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty
    Note: Parse field structure: name_len(4) + name_data + tag_len(4) + tag_data + type_id(4) + field_offset(4) + field_flags(4)
    Let name_len be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, offset)
    If name_len is equal to 0 or name_len is greater than 256:
    Return Empty Let name_offset be offset + 4
    If name_offset + name_len is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty Let field_name be String::substring(type_data, name_offset, name_len) Let tag_len_offset be name_offset + name_len
    Let tag_len be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, tag_len_offset)
    If tag_len is greater than 1024: Note: Reasonable tag limit
    Return Empty Let tag_offset be tag_len_offset + 4
    Let field_tag be ""
    If tag_len is greater than 0:
    If tag_offset + tag_len is greater than String::length(type_data):
    Return Empty
    Set field_tag to String::substring(type_data, tag_offset, tag_len) Let type_id_offset be tag_offset + tag_len
    Let field_type_id be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, type_id_offset) Let field_offset_offset be type_id_offset + 4
    Let field_memory_offset be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, field_offset_offset) Let flags_offset be field_offset_offset + 4
    Let field_flags be read_uint32_from_bytes(type_data, flags_offset)
    Note: Parse field properties from flags
    Let is_exported be (field_flags and 1) is not equal to 0
    Let is_anonymous be (field_flags and 2) is not equal to 0
    Let is_pointer be (field_flags and 4) is not equal to 0
    Note: Parse struct tags
    Let parsed_tags be parse_go_struct_tags(field_tag) Let go_field be GoField with:
    name as field_name,
    field_type as resolve_go_type_name(field_type_id),
    tag as field_tag,
    parsed_tags as parsed_tags,
    offset as field_memory_offset,
    is_exported as is_exported,
    is_anonymous as is_anonymous,
    is_pointer as is_pointer,
    field_flags as field_flags Return Some with value go_field

Note: Go Signature Parsing
Process parse_go_method_signature that takes signature as String returns Dictionary[String, List[String]]:
    Let result be new Dictionary
    Set result["parameters"] to new List
    Set result["returns"] to new List
    Note: Simple signature parsing - looks for func(params) returns
    Let func_start be String::index_of(signature, "func(")
    If func_start is equal to -1:
    Return result Let params_start be func_start + 5 Note: Length of "func("
    Let params_end be String::index_of_from(signature, ")", params_start)
    If params_end is equal to -1:
    Return result
    Note: Extract parameter types
    Let params_str be String::substring(signature, params_start, params_end - params_start)
    If String::length(params_str) is greater than 0:
    Let param_types be String::split(params_str, ",")
    For Each param_type in param_types:
    Let cleaned_param be String::trim(param_type)
    If String::length(cleaned_param) is greater than 0:
    Add extract_go_type_from_param(cleaned_param) to result["parameters"]
    Note: Extract return types
    Let returns_start be params_end + 1
    If returns_start is less than String::length(signature):
    Let returns_str be String::trim(String::substring(signature, returns_start, String::length(signature) minus returns_start))
    If String::length(returns_str) is greater than 0:
    If String::starts_with(returns_str, "(") and String::ends_with(returns_str, ")"):
Note: Multiple return values
    Let returns_inner be String::substring(returns_str, 1, String::length(returns_str) minus 2)
    Let return_types be String::split(returns_inner, ",")
    For Each return_type in return_types:
    Let cleaned_return be String::trim(return_type)
    If String::length(cleaned_return) is greater than 0:
    Add cleaned_return to result["returns"]
    Otherwise:
Note: Single return value
    Add returns_str to result["returns"] Return result

Process parse_go_struct_tags that takes tag_string as String returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Let tags be new Dictionary If String::length(tag_string) is equal to 0:
    Return tags
    Note: Parse Go struct tags format: `key:"value" key2:"value2"`
    Let i be 0
    Let tag_len be String::length(tag_string) While i is less than tag_len:
Note: Skip whitespace
    While i is less than tag_len and String::char_at(tag_string, i) is equal to " ":
    Set i to i + 1 If i is greater than or equal to tag_len:
    Break
    Note: Find key
    Let key_start be i
    While i is less than tag_len and String::char_at(tag_string, i) is not equal to ":":
    Set i to i + 1 If i is greater than or equal to tag_len:
    Break Let key be String::substring(tag_string, key_start, i - key_start)
    Set i to i + 1 Note: Skip ":"
    Note: Skip whitespace and opening quote
    While i is less than tag_len and (String::char_at(tag_string, i) is equal to " " or String::char_at(tag_string, i) is equal to "\""):
    Set i to i + 1
    Note: Find value
    Let value_start be i
    While i is less than tag_len and String::char_at(tag_string, i) is not equal to "\"":
    Set i to i + 1 Let value be String::substring(tag_string, value_start, i - value_start)
    Set tags[key] to value Set i to i + 1 Note: Skip closing quote Return tags

Process extract_go_type_from_param that takes param_str as String returns String:
Note: Remove parameter names and extract just the type
    Let parts be String::split(param_str, " ")
    If Collections::length(parts) is greater than 1:
Note: Has parameter name, return the type (last part)
    Return Collections::last(parts)
    Otherwise:
Note: Just the type
    Return String::trim(param_str)

Process resolve_go_type_name that takes type_id as Integer returns String:
Note: This would normally look up type names from a type registry
Note: For now, return a basic type mapping
    If type_id is equal to 1:
    Return "bool"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 2:
    Return "int"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 3:
    Return "int8"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 4:
    Return "int16"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 5:
    Return "int32"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 6:
    Return "int64"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 7:
    Return "uint"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 8:
    Return "uint8"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 9:
    Return "uint16"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 10:
    Return "uint32"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 11:
    Return "uint64"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 12:
    Return "float32"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 13:
    Return "float64"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 14:
    Return "string"
    Otherwise if type_id is equal to 15:
    Return "interface{}"
    Otherwise:
    Return "type_" + String::from_integer(type_id)

Note: Binary Data Reading Functions
Process read_uint32_from_bytes that takes data as String and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    If offset + 4 is greater than String::length(data):
    Return 0
    Note: Read little-endian 32-bit unsigned integer
    Let byte0 be String::char_code_at(data, offset)
    Let byte1 be String::char_code_at(data, offset + 1)
    Let byte2 be String::char_code_at(data, offset + 2)
    Let byte3 be String::char_code_at(data, offset + 3) Return byte0 + (byte1 multiplied by 256) + (byte2 multiplied by 65536) + (byte3 multiplied by 16777216)

Process read_uint16_from_bytes that takes data as String and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    If offset + 2 is greater than String::length(data):
    Return 0
    Note: Read little-endian 16-bit unsigned integer
    Let byte0 be String::char_code_at(data, offset)
    Let byte1 be String::char_code_at(data, offset + 1) Return byte0 + (byte1 multiplied by 256)

Process read_uint8_from_bytes that takes data as String and offset as Integer returns Integer:
    If offset + 1 is greater than String::length(data):
    Return 0 Return String::char_code_at(data, offset)

Note: Go Type System Integration
Process create_go_type_registry that takes returns Dictionary[Integer, String]:
    Let registry be new Dictionary
    Note: Basic types
    Set registry[1] to "bool"
    Set registry[2] to "int"
    Set registry[3] to "int8"
    Set registry[4] to "int16"
    Set registry[5] to "int32"
    Set registry[6] to "int64"
    Set registry[7] to "uint"
    Set registry[8] to "uint8"
    Set registry[9] to "uint16"
    Set registry[10] to "uint32"
    Set registry[11] to "uint64"
    Set registry[12] to "float32"
    Set registry[13] to "float64"
    Set registry[14] to "string"
    Set registry[15] to "interface{}"
    Set registry[16] to "chan"
    Set registry[17] to "map"
    Set registry[18] to "slice"
    Set registry[19] to "array"
    Set registry[20] to "struct"
    Set registry[21] to "func"
    Set registry[22] to "pointer"
    Return registry

Process validate_go_method_info that takes method as GoMethod returns Boolean:
Note: Validate method information
    If String::length(method.name) is equal to 0:
    Return false If String::length(method.signature) is equal to 0:
    Return false If method.method_index is less than 0:
    Return false
    Note: Check if parameter and return type counts make sense
    Let param_count be Collections::length(method.parameter_types)
    Let return_count be Collections::length(method.return_types) If param_count is greater than 32: Note: Reasonable limit
    Return false If return_count is greater than 8: Note: Reasonable limit
    Return false Return true

Process validate_go_field_info that takes field as GoField returns Boolean:
Note: Validate field information
    If String::length(field.name) is equal to 0:
    Return false If String::length(field.field_type) is equal to 0:
    Return false If field.offset is less than 0:
    Return false Return true